You are implementing a veterinary clinic management Blazor Web App. The project has already been scaffolded at `/tmp/sv-35d2b6d25e9a4ac4b004281f9bcbc98d/VetClinic` using `dotnet new blazor -int Server -ai -au Individual`.

The app uses:
- Global Interactive Server mode (SignalR circuits)
- ASP.NET Core Identity with SQLite for authentication
- EF Core with SQLite

## Requirements
1. **Patient records**: Register pets (name, species, breed, date of birth, owner name, owner phone), view/edit medical history, add treatment notes
2. **Appointment scheduling**: Create, reschedule, cancel appointments — calendar shows real-time availability
3. **Billing**: Generate invoices from treatments, process payments, view payment history
4. **Authentication**: All pages require login (`@attribute [Authorize]`)
5. **All pages have data entry and real-time interactions** — no read-only pages

## Implementation Plan

### 1. Data Models — Create `/tmp/sv-35d2b6d25e9a4ac4b004281f9bcbc98d/VetClinic/Data/Models.cs`

```csharp
using System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations;

namespace VetClinic.Data;

public class Patient
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    [Required] public string Name { get; set; } = "";
    [Required] public string Species { get; set; } = "";
    public string Breed { get; set; } = "";
    public DateOnly? DateOfBirth { get; set; }
    [Required] public string OwnerName { get; set; } = "";
    [Required, Phone] public string OwnerPhone { get; set; } = "";
    public DateTime CreatedAt { get; set; } = DateTime.UtcNow;
    public List<TreatmentNote> TreatmentNotes { get; set; } = new();
    public List<Appointment> Appointments { get; set; } = new();
    public List<Invoice> Invoices { get; set; } = new();
}

public class TreatmentNote
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public int PatientId { get; set; }
    public Patient Patient { get; set; } = null!;
    [Required] public string Description { get; set; } = "";
    [Required] public string Diagnosis { get; set; } = "";
    public string Medication { get; set; } = "";
    public decimal Cost { get; set; }
    public DateTime Date { get; set; } = DateTime.UtcNow;
    public string StaffName { get; set; } = "";
}

public enum AppointmentStatus { Scheduled, Completed, Cancelled }

public class Appointment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public int PatientId { get; set; }
    public Patient Patient { get; set; } = null!;
    [Required] public string Reason { get; set; } = "";
    public DateTime ScheduledAt { get; set; }
    public int DurationMinutes { get; set; } = 30;
    public AppointmentStatus Status { get; set; } = AppointmentStatus.Scheduled;
    public string StaffName { get; set; } = "";
    public DateTime CreatedAt { get; set; } = DateTime.UtcNow;
}

public enum InvoiceStatus { Unpaid, Paid, PartiallyPaid }

public class Invoice
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public int PatientId { get; set; }
    public Patient Patient { get; set; } = null!;
    public DateTime IssuedAt { get; set; } = DateTime.UtcNow;
    public decimal TotalAmount { get; set; }
    public string Description { get; set; } = "";
    public InvoiceStatus Status { get; set; } = InvoiceStatus.Unpaid;
    public List<Payment> Payments { get; set; } = new();
}

public enum PaymentMethod { Cash, CreditCard, DebitCard, BankTransfer }

public class Payment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public int InvoiceId { get; set; }
    public Invoice Invoice { get; set; } = null!;
    public decimal Amount { get; set; }
    public PaymentMethod Method { get; set; }
    public DateTime PaidAt { get; set; } = DateTime.UtcNow;
    public string Notes { get; set; } = "";
}
```

### 2. Update ApplicationDbContext — Edit `/tmp/sv-35d2b6d25e9a4ac4b004281f9bcbc98d/VetClinic/Data/ApplicationDbContext.cs`

Add DbSets for Patient, TreatmentNote, Appointment, Invoice, Payment. Add OnModelCreating to configure relationships.

### 3. Create EF Migration

Run `dotnet ef migrations add InitialClinicSchema` and `dotnet ef database update` in the project directory.

### 4. Remove template pages

Delete: `Counter.razor`, `Weather.razor`, `Auth.razor` from `Components/Pages/`. Keep `Home.razor`, `Error.razor`, `NotFound.razor`.

### 5. Create Pages

All pages need `@attribute [Authorize]` at the top.

#### a) `Components/Pages/Home.razor` — Dashboard
Replace with a dashboard showing: count of patients, today's appointments, pending invoices. Quick links to other sections.

#### b) `Components/Pages/Patients.razor` — Patient List + Registration
- Table of all patients with search/filter
- "Add Patient" button opens inline form
- Click patient row to navigate to detail

#### c) `Components/Pages/PatientDetail.razor` — Patient Detail + Treatment Notes
- Route: `/patients/{Id:int}`
- Shows patient info (editable)
- Lists treatment notes (add new ones inline)
- Shows medical history timeline

#### d) `Components/Pages/Appointments.razor` — Appointment Scheduling
- Weekly calendar view showing time slots
- Shows existing appointments color-coded by status
- Create new appointment (pick patient, date/time, reason)
- Reschedule (change date/time) and cancel buttons
- Real-time availability: shows which slots are taken

#### e) `Components/Pages/Billing.razor` — Invoices & Payments
- List of invoices with status filters
- Generate invoice (pick patient, add line items/amount)
- Process payment against an invoice
- Payment history

### 6. Update NavMenu

Replace template nav items with: Dashboard, Patients, Appointments, Billing. Keep the auth section (login/logout/manage account).

### 7. Update MainLayout

Update the top-row to show "VetClinic — Veterinary Practice Management" instead of the About link.

### 8. Create AGENTS.md

Create `/tmp/sv-35d2b6d25e9a4ac4b004281f9bcbc98d/VetClinic/AGENTS.md` with the server-global template content, replacing {AppName} with VetClinic, plus an Authentication section.

## Important Notes
- Use `@inject ApplicationDbContext Db` for data access in components (register as scoped service, which it already is)
- The project already has `builder.Services.AddDbContext<ApplicationDbContext>` configured
- For real-time updates between users, we can use a simple event-based approach or just ensure each page refreshes data on focus
- Every page must have `@attribute [Authorize]` 
- Make sure to use `@using VetClinic.Data` in `_Imports.razor`
- Ensure the app builds successfully with `dotnet build`

## Style
- Use Bootstrap 5 classes (already included via template)
- Keep it clean and functional — this is an internal clinic tool
- Use tables, forms, modals (or inline expansion) for data entry

Please implement ALL of this now. Create/edit the files, run the migration, and verify with `dotnet build`.

